                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. Occasionally, the word God is rubricated in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#48v"/>)</desc>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#110r"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#117r #117v"/> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d01"><locus target="#iiv(erso)"/><desc>Representation of an altar. Below is a pen trial</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d02"><locus target="#125v"/><desc> Ornate <ref type ="authFile" corresp="AT1071Cross"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d03"><locus target="#140v"/><desc>Excerpt from Psalm 151 with an ornate symbol, functioning as a pen trial</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="d04">
                    5.	Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #7v #15r #23r #32v #40r #45v #53v #63r #70v #75v #87r #97v #100r #105v #110v #120r"/> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#1r"/> (line of black dots);
                    <locus target="#138r"/> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a01">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#138v"/>: An Asmat Prayer for protection against demons, an Arabic text written in Gə‘əz characters.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">የጋኔን፡ የማስቀርብ፡ ቢስምላሒ፡ አርማኒ፡ እራሒም፡ ለሚኩኒ፡ አለዚነ፡ ከፈሩ፡ ምን፡ አህሊል፡ ኪታቤ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a02">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>": Note of secondary ownership, in purple ink and blue ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e01">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #126rv #139r #139v #140r"/>: blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e02">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 22
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e03">
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    green yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#15 #32 #45 #70"/>;
                    black yarn is sewn into fore edge of <locus target="#23"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e04">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 5 (incorrectly numbered on <locus target="#49r"/>) and 12
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e05">
                    <desc>
                    Space was left on Psalm 118 for the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters, but they were not written
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e06">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#4v #5r #6r #9v #10v"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#12v #14r #19r #23v #24v"/>, etc.);
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#121v"/>, line 14);
                    erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#100r"/>);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#17v #26r #28r #35r #44r"/>, etc.)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
